sentences: Jordan Mackenzie Smith (born November 4, 1993) is an American singer, songwriter, and musician from Harlan, Kentucky.
In 2015 he gained national recognition when he won season 9 of the singing competition The Voice.
Jordan Smith was born on November 4, 1993,  in Whitley County, Kentucky, to Kelley and Geri Smith (n√©e Saylor), both of whom are musicians.
In 2012, he won the Poke Sallet Idol competition at the annual Poke Sallet festival.
The Voice (2015)
Smith came to national attention in 2015 during his participation on season nine of The Voice.

"For week two of the live shows, Smith began "Great Is Thy Faithfulness" by singing a cappella, then accompanied himself on piano; the performance made Smith the first artist of the season to reach No. 1 in sales in the iTunes Store, ahead of "Hello" by Adele.
"Great Is Thy Faithfulness" landed on the Billboard magazine charts as well; it placed at No. 30 on the Hot 100, and was No. 1 on the Christian Songs chart for two straight weeks.
Within 30 minutes, the single was the best selling song in the iTunes Store, knocking "Hello" from the top spot for a second time.
As of December 2015, Jordan Smith was the highest selling artist ever to compete on The Voice.

One week after his victory, Smith made history on Billboard's Christian Songs chart; he became the first artist ever to hold the top two positions concurrently when his cover of "Mary, Did You Know?" overtook "Hallelujah" as the No. 1 song.
The Voice: Jordan Smith: The Complete Season 9 Collection was released in December 2015, entering the Billboard 200 albums chart at No. 11, earning "Hot Shot Debut" honors.
He was also named the 2015 Kentucky Monthly Kentuckian of the Year.
